opendcl-controls — full common-control catalogue
================================================

See also: opendcl.plan, opendcl-renderer-scaffold.issue,
opendcl-runtime-core.issue, opendcl-conformance.issue.

Context
-------

After Phase 1 (`opendcl-runtime-core.issue` +
`opendcl-renderer-scaffold.issue`), Button / Label / EditBox /
OK / Cancel land. Real OpenDCL applications need substantially
more: TreeView, ListView with sortable columns, PropertyGrid,
ImageList-backed image buttons, tabbed pages, group boxes,
ComboBox with autocomplete, DateTimePicker, RichEdit, dockable
palette tab stacks. This issue captures the bulk extension of the
catalogue.

The scaffolding is fixed: each control is a triple of
  - a runtime constructor (instantiated from the project tree),
  - a wire encoding (under `(:control-create FID …)` and
    associated `(:property-set …)` / `(:list-populate …)`),
  - a Qt-side materialiser plus property-map entry.

Suggested ordering (revisit per scenario need)
----------------------------------------------

  1. Layout and containers
       - Tab / TabPage      (QTabWidget / QWidget pages)
       - GroupBox           (QGroupBox)
       - Panel              (QFrame with layout)
       - Splitter           (QSplitter)
     Layout containers come first because every later control needs
     a layout parent.

  2. Choice / selection
       - CheckBox           (QCheckBox)
       - RadioButton        (QRadioButton + QButtonGroup)
       - ComboBox           (QComboBox; editable + autocomplete)
       - ListBox            (QListWidget — single / multi select)

  3. Tabular / hierarchical
       - ListView           (QTreeView with QStandardItemModel,
                              columns, sort indicator)
       - TreeView           (QTreeWidget for V1 simplicity;
                              switch to MVC later if needed)

  4. Rich-edit and images
       - RichEdit           (QTextEdit; subset of RTF in V1)
       - ImageButton        (QToolButton with QIcon)
       - StaticImage        (QLabel with QPixmap)
       - ImageList          (resource-side: indexed pixmap registry
                              shared by image-bearing controls)

  5. Time / date / numeric
       - DateTimePicker     (QDateTimeEdit)
       - SpinBox            (QSpinBox / QDoubleSpinBox)
       - Slider             (QSlider)
       - ProgressBar        (QProgressBar; read-only host-driven)

  6. PropertyGrid           (QTreeView with custom delegate, or
                              third-party widget — research at the
                              ticket stage)

For each control:
  - the property-map entry (OpenDCL property name → Qt property
    accessor) goes in the renderer's
    `opendcl_property_map.{hpp,cpp}` (per
    opendcl-renderer-scaffold.issue);
  - the AutoLISP builtin coverage stays at the *generic* property
    surface (`dcl_Control_GetProperty` / `SetProperty`) plus the
    list-manipulation family
    (`dcl_List_Add`, `dcl_List_Insert`, `dcl_List_Remove`,
    `dcl_List_Clear`, `dcl_List_Get`, `dcl_List_Set`,
    `dcl_Tree_AddNode`, `dcl_Tree_RemoveNode`, …);
  - the wire messages stay within the catalogue defined by
    `opendcl-wire-protocol.issue`.

In scope
--------

For each control above:
  - constructor in clautolisp/autolisp-opendcl;
  - property-map entries on the Qt side;
  - mock-renderer fixture so MockHost-driven tests cover the
    builtin behaviour without a display.

Out of scope
------------

  - ActiveX/COM host controls. They require a CAD bridge and are
    deferred to V2 (noted in `opendcl.plan`).
  - Per-platform native renderers.
  - Cosmetic theming (let Qt do its default thing in V1).

Acceptance criteria
-------------------

  - Each control category has at least one scenario in the
    conformance corpus (`opendcl-conformance.issue`) that exercises
    construction + a representative property get/set + at least
    one event.
  - PropertyGrid renders something usable for the upstream sample
    that uses it (one of the demo `.odcl` files); accept that V1's
    PropertyGrid won't match every quirk of the MFC implementation.
  - autolisp-spec "OpenDCL Controls" subsection lists every
    implemented control and its supported properties / events,
    cross-referenced to the upstream reference.

Notes
-----

Don't try to land everything in one drop. Break the work into
per-control or per-cluster PRs once Phase 1 is green, ideally one
PR per row in the ordering above. Each PR adds one or two corpus
scenarios.
